oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cabinet card of an unidentified post-Civil War soldier
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This cabinet card shows a US soldier from the 1880s-1890s time frame. He wears sergeant chevrons on his uniform coat and has the insignia of the 3rd Infantry on his cap. The photographer was from Rockwood, Tenn. This may be a soldier from the Tenn. National Guard. or Tenn. State Guard.
